The paper deals with the problem of finding the minimum radius for two congruent closed disks that completely cover a convex polygon. This problem is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and approximation algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithm proposed in the paper uses space-efficient techniques, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The analysis of the algorithm involves mathematical optimization and approximation techniques, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the algorithm, which is relevant to complexity theory (cs.CC).
